load ../compaction-epoch-lifecycle.maude

--- Coverage: the trigger begins exactly one summarizer round.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-COMPACTION-EPOCH-LIFECYCLE :
  armed
  =>* summarizing .

--- Coverage: the round applies as the single atomic prefix rewrite (prefix installed,
--- epoch marked spent).
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-COMPACTION-EPOCH-LIFECYCLE :
  armed
  =>* prefix applied .

--- Coverage: after apply, a main turn appends to the held prefix (a cache hit), never
--- rewriting it.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-COMPACTION-EPOCH-LIFECYCLE :
  armed turnPending
  =>* prefix tail applied .

--- Bite: at-most-once-per-epoch. The RESIDUAL soup var makes `refired` in ANY
--- reachable state a solution, so No solution proves no second summarization fires
--- for the same epoch (there is no re-arm rule producing a fresh `armed`).
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-COMPACTION-EPOCH-LIFECYCLE :
  armed
  =>* refired RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: atomic apply / no half-rewrite. No reachable state rewrites the prefix while
--- the summarizer round is in flight -- [append] requires a `prefix`, which only the
--- atomic [apply] produces, so a mid-summary prefix rewrite is unreachable.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-COMPACTION-EPOCH-LIFECYCLE :
  armed turnPending
  =>* prefixDuringSummary RESIDUAL:Cfg .
